3.2 Hardness intensity diagram
"The hardness intensity diagram (HID) for MAXI J1631-472 during
the 2018/19 outburst is shown in Fig. 2. Fig. 2 (a) shows the HID
for the full duration of the outburst, with the colour bar representing
the time evolution. As seen in Fig. 2 (b), MAXI J1631-472 shows
a rapid rise in photon flux as it changes from quiescence to peak
flux in roughly 25 days while the spectral state changes from hard
(HRâˆ¼9) to soft (HRâˆ¼1.2) during this period. The decline of the
X-ray photon flux occurs while the system is in the soft state, during
which the radio flare is seen to occur (colour-bar in Fig. 2 (c))).
As the X-ray photon flux continues to decline, it reaches a point
